                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "VrXQs",
                      "fill": "$muted-fg",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": 672,
                      "content": "We classify rhetorical frames in Congressional speeches using weak supervision from the Policy Frames Codebook, then evaluate both lexical and contextual models. The results show strong stereotypical lexical patterns while also confirming the value of deeper contextual signals.",
